This software is awesome by itself. It's now my main tool for any image creating/ editing that I do . I don't even use the animating functionality that much, but even when I'm just working with static image files, it's perfect for me. I consider this software to be better than photoshop for basically four reasons:

- Aseprite has a intuitive animation system;
- Aseprite is pretty much easy to use;
- Aseprite has an old-school UI. Not that I prefer old-school UIs, but that this software is MUCH LIGHTER because of that.
- Aseprite. IS. MUCH. CHEAPER.

So, that's what I think.  You can make your own conclusions, after all.
